    <note>Yang(2) Wenguang [16263] He became an officer when he earned distinction in a campaign against bandits. He later served under Di(1) Qing [8127] in the Vietnamese campaign and later distinguished himself under Han(1) Qi's [630] overall command as a general in the Xi Xia wars. He died before he could carry out the plans he presented to retake the Beijing area from the Khitan. CBD, 4, 3153-4.</note>
